aVAARP members have countless opportunities during a night out on the town or on vacation. Finding out what to see, what to eat, or where to stay is as easy as going online at the AARP website or looking through the organization\u2019s benefits guide.\u000a\u000aAlong with great savings on travel, merchandise, and insurance, members also receive significant discounts on entertainment, dining, and hotel accommodations. For $16 a year, an AARP membership card makes a night out even more exciting. It costs only $12 the first year by selecting auto-renew.\u000a\u000aSpecial: Loophole Can Qualify Seniors for $20,500 Check\u000a\u000aThere is so much to do as an AARP member, but here are some suggestions:\u000a\u000aWhat to See\u000a\u000aEnjoy a movie at any Regal Cinema nationwide at discounted prices. AARP members can purchase tickets online, print them out, and use them immediately. Or they can have eTickets sent to an email address.\u000a\u000aExperience an exciting Las Vegas show, not just in Vegas but in cities near you. Members get up to 20-percent discounts on Cirque du Soleil tickets for touring shows and in Vegas.\u000a\u000aMembers can take advantage of discount travel packages to such diverse locations as Vegas, New York, Seattle, Honolulu, New Orleans, or Orlando by searching online at the AARP Travel Center\u000a\u000aTip: How to Retire Comfortably on $2,000\u000a\u000aOrlando offers some of the greatest theme parks in the world. Honolulu provides the famous Waikiki Beach with Diamond Head as a backdrop. New Orleans boasts of a fabulous night life with live jazz music in clubs in the French Quarter. Seattle, known as the jewel of the Pacific Northwest, has a beautiful environment, unique culture, and vibrant music scene, along with the landmark Space Needle.\u000a\u000aWhat to Eat\u000a\u000aWhether traveling on vacation or just dining out locally, AARP members can find 10- to 15-percent savings at such restaurants as Carrabba\u2019s Italian Grill, Denny\u2019s, Outback Steakhouse, the Oceanaire Seafood Room, and sweetFrog Premium Frozen Yogurt.\u000a\u000amembers can find 10- to 15-percent savings at such restaurants as Carrabba\u2019s Italian Grill, Denny\u2019s, Outback Steakhouse, the Oceanaire Seafood Room, and sweetFrog Premium Frozen Yogurt. Members can also take in the finest cuisine during trips around the country. Las Vegas has such celebrity chef restaurants as Bobby Flay\u2019s Mesa Grill. Manhattan offers trendy eateries before a show or visiting the many museums. New Orleans has extraordinary food for a night out.\u000a\u000aBut any location has its special delicacies, and AARP members are sure to find savings just about anywhere they go.\u000a\u000aImportant: Gingrich and Reagan Video Goes Viral. See It Now\u000a\u000aWhere to Stay
