aVAlec Baldwin was back on television as Donald Trump \u2014 mocking the president's rally in Arizona this week.\u000a\u000aBaldwin appeared on "Saturday Night Life: Weekend Update Summer Edition" on Thursday.\u000a\u000aThe skit opened with Baldwin's Trump taking the stage to address the rally.\u000a\u000a"As we know there was a tragic victim that came out of Charlottesville \u2026. me," said Baldwin's Trump. "Folks, the media has treated me so unfairly by reporting my entire remarks even the bad ones."\u000a\u000aHe also ribbed President Trump over Afghanistan saying: "They won't tell you about my accomplishments, but I've done so much. First off, last night, I solved Afghanistan \u2026 solved. Sat down with our military, we looked at the map and I asked the hard questions like: 'Which one is Afghanistan?'\u000a\u000aThe Hill noted Baldwin regularly lampooned the president on "Saturday Night Live" during the last season before appearing on the summer version of the show.\u000a\u000aBaldwin has confirmed he will return as Trump on "Saturday Night Live" in the fall.
