rries, kiwi, bell peppers, broccoli, and Brussels sprouts.have unsaturated fats and essential fatty acids that are called the \u201chealthy fats.\u201d Walnuts, Brazil nuts, flaxseeds, and chia seeds have the healthy fats that reduce inflammation to significantly improve the skin, Jacqueline Banks, a certified holistic health counselor, wrote in an article for Fox News . Almonds are also known to strengthen cell membranes for skin health.is packed with protein and vitamins to enhance the immune system, necessary to maintain vibrant, clear and young-looking skin, TotalBeauty said. Yogurt and other dairy products contain vitamin A, which protects the skin from environmental damage and overexposure to the sun that can cause premature wrinkles.
