aVPolitical commentator Michael Reagan told Newsmax TV on Thursday that Donald Trump is running his presidency "kind of like a dictatorship" and he is alienating the Republican leadership crucial to getting his agenda passed in Congress.\u000a\u000a"It's about Donald Trump," the eldest son of former President Ronald Reagan told Bill Tucker on "Newsmax Now." "You're seeing the way he runs his business, kind of like a dictatorship.\u000a\u000a"It's about him all the time."\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-Verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator does not have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2013 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we will connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2013 Click Here Now\u000a\u000aTrump has repeatedly slammed Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell on Twitter over the chamber's failure to repeal and replace Obamacare last month \u2014 and he included House Speaker Paul Ryan in his attack on the leaders as he ripped the national debt as a "mess."\u000a\u000a"He attacks the very people he's going to need to really get some things passed in Washington \u2014 McConnell, Ryan, the rest of them," Reagan told Tucker.\u000a\u000a"And, so, the Republicans will always have trouble trying to tell you the good things that they've been able to do \u2014 the bills they've been able to pass \u2014 because they're being drowned out by Trump each and every day.\u000a\u000a"The president is finding out that running a business and getting things done from the dictatorial position as the president of your own organization is a lot different than Washington," he added.\u000a\u000a"That's a different art of the deal than running a business \u2014 and he hasn't yet found that out.\u000a\u000a"He has to find out how to work the edges to get things ultimately done," Reagan said. "He doesn't need to go to war with his own party."
