aVBodybuilder Rich Piana died Friday, nearly three weeks after being placed in a medically induced coma following a medical emergency. He was 46.\u000a\u000aThe District Six Medical Examiner in Florida confirmed Piana's death, TMZ reported. He was rushed to a Florida hospital Aug. 7 after collapsing while getting a haircut.\u000a\u000aThe former Mr. California's estranged wife, Sara Piana, posted about his death on Facebook.\u000a\u000aPolice found more than 20 bottles of steroids at his apartment at the time of his collapse, TMZ reported. His girlfriend, Chanel Jansen, said he hit his head during the fall.\u000a\u000aPiana was a steroid user for more than 25 years, but spoke out about the dangers of the drugs on YouTube.\u000a\u000a\u201cIf you have the choice to stay natural or do steroids, stay natural. There\u2019s no reason to do steroids, you\u2019re only hurting your body, you\u2019re hurting yourself,\u201d he said on YouTube last year, while acknowledging that for professional bobybuilders steroids were unavoidable.\u000a\u000aPiana began bodybuilding at age 15, Men's Health reported. He won many fitness competitions, including Mr. California with an overall perfect score in 1998.\u000a\u000aHe was outspoken on social media, with 1.2 million Instagram followers and almost 960,000 subscribers on YouTube, the magazine noted.\u000a\u000aPiana was remembered on Twitter.\u000a\u000aRIP Rich Piana. Even though he looked pretty intimidating, anyone that knew the real him knew he was one of the nicest guys in the industry. \u2014 ROB TRAMONTE | GC\u2122 \u2316 (@RobTramonte) August 25, 2017\u000a\u000aRIP Rich Piana\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aGone too soon brother. What a sad day, can't even believe it's true...truly heartbreaking. pic.twitter.com/rzg4N5r30B \u2014 JAMES MOONEY | GC\u2122 (@JamesMooneyGC) August 25, 2017\u000a\u000aVery sad about Rich Piana.Something for you young guys to take away from this is don't abuse tf out of steroids, they do more harm than good \u2014 Bryce (@bryce_lugviel) August 25, 2017\u000a\u000aRip to the legend of Rich Piana it was an honor meeting you last year pic.twitter.com/Ik4ekRCUNa \u2014 BIG BALLER JACOBO (@JacobGoodsell) August 25, 2017
