aVVote Now:\u000a\u000aWho Is Your Favorite Actor of All Time?\u000a\u000aUrgent:\u000a\u000aWho Should the GOP Nominate in 2016? Vote Here Now\u000a\u000aVote Now:\u000a\u000aWhich of These Actresses Stands the Test of Time?\u000a\u000a\u201cComing out\u201d these days in Hollywood has nothing to do with sexual preference, but it has a lot to do with politics.In the old days, being labeled a Republican or conservative was a train wreck for an actor or actress' career. Not anymore.Groups like Friends of Abe, a conclave of Hollywood and entertainment professionals, are thriving. Actors like the late Charlton Heston, an outspoken Republican and advocate of gun freedom, helped pave the way.One caveat here: The conservative-leaning celebrities listed here may not be going to a Ted Cruz rally anytime soon. They are better described as Hollywood contrarians; they don\u2019t typically advocate any hardcore political agenda.Instead, they are for a new openness in Hollywood, and don\u2019t accept the old industry standard that one has to be a card-carrying member of the Democratic Party to find career advancement.Oftentimes these conservatives are more libertarian than traditional, button-down Republicans.Whatever their stripes, they are a unique and exciting breed changing Hollywood and, we hope, America for the better.Here, Newsmax has compiled a list of 50 influential leaders of this cultural minority who have bucked Hollywood\u2019s liberal establishment and thrived.\u2014 The actor and director famously trashed President Barack Obama in 2012 at the Republican National Convention and stirred up a firestorm of liberal griping with his patriotic film, "American Sniper."\u2014 The star of the "Rocky" and "Rambo" series of hit movies is not shy about voicing his Christian conservative beliefs. He backed Sen. John McCain's presidential bid in 2008 and recently told evangelist Pat Robertson, "I have surrendered my life to Jesus Christ."\u2014 The "Home Improvement" actor once told Sean Hannity he is a \u201cfiscal conservative\u201d who \u201clike[s] problem solving." He has endorsed Gov. John Kasich for president.\u2014 The "Duck Dynasty" star is known for his strong Christian faith and conservative politics. He recently endorsed Donald Trump for president and also scored a gig as a Fox News contributor with an eponymous podcast.\u2014 The award-winning actor best known for "Once Upon a Time in America," "Casino," and "White House Down" is well-known for his conservative views and has endorsed Sen. Ted Cruz for president in 2016.\u2014 The "Forrest Gump" star is one of the founding members of the Friends of Abe, a Hollywood conservative group.\u2014 Formerly known as Olympic decathlon champion Bruce Jenner, Caitlyn has declared herself a Republican and has publicly favored Ted Cruz's presidential campaign.\u2014 The former Nixon and Ford speechwriter, TV game show host, actor, and prolific writer is a confirmed conservative and registered Republican, an opponent of legalized abortion, and a one-time endorser of John McCain.\u2014 The actor who starred on ABC's "Growing Pains" is an Evangelical Christian with strong conservative beliefs. In 2014, he starred in "Saving Christmas," a comedic Christian film that sought to "put Christ back in Christmas."\u2014 The host of "The Price Is Right" considers himself a libertarian and is a board member of the Reason Foundation, a libertarian think tank.\u2014 The standup comic and former "Saturday Night Live" star and one-time Democrat today is a well-known conservative political pundit who regularly appears on Fox News' "The O'Reilly Factor."\u2014 The "Magnum P.I." star endorsed Sen. John McCain for president in 2008 and is a board member with the National Rifle Association.t \u2014 The "Midnight Cowboy," "Deliverance," and "Coming Home" star and father of actress Angelina Jolie switched from liberal to conservative and has endorsed Donald Trump for president.\u2014 "The Terminator" and "Predator" star and worldwide bodybuilding champ served two terms as the Republican governor of California. He is backing John Kasich for president and recently shared a "tele-town hall" meeting with the Ohio governor.\u2014 The "Duck Dynasty" reality television star, duck hunter, committed Christian, and businessman has addressed the Conservative Political Action Conference and received the Andrew Breitbart Defender of the First Amendment Award.\u2014 The "Motor City Madman" hard rocker, big game hunter, actor, and songwriter is one of the best-known ultra-conservatives in America, a strong supporter of the Republican Party, and a board member with the National Rifle Association.\u2014 The "Hercules" and "God's Not Dead" star, with strong conservative, Christian beliefs, has called out Hollywood's liberal hypocrisy, ranted against President Barack Obama, and spoken out about national controversies like the Ferguson protests.\u2014 The star of "The Godfather" and "The Judge" backed Mitt Romney in 2012 and narrated a video for the Republican National Convention in 2008. He raised $800,000 for Romney and appeared on stage with Sarah Palin and John McCain.\u2014 Though she doesn't discuss her personal politics publicly, Locklear is reportedly a registered Republican.\u2014 A one-time supporter of the Democratic Party, the former "West Wing" actor's Twitter feed appears to lean more to the right as of late, calling out President Barack Obama over Benghazi, voicing support for our heroes, and accusing CNN anchors of "holding water for Obama." He also supported Arnold Schwarzenegger's campaign in 2003.\u2014 The "Godfather" star and Hollywood tough guy has termed himself an "ultra-conservative." He says he is a fan of Fox News and only watches Bill O'Reilly.\u2014 The "Frasier" star backed Rudy Giuliani for mayor of New York and founded the RightNetwork, a conservative entertainment company.\u2014 A self-described "hardcore libertarian," Russell has spoken out about his political beliefs in the past, ripping the left's stance that gun control could limit terrorism. "If you think gun control is going to change the terrorists\u2019 point of view, I think you\u2019re, like, out of your mind," he told a reporter while promoting "The Hateful Eight" last year.\u2014 Doherty, a mainstay of "Beverly Hills 90210" and "Charmed," has termed herself a "conservative" and an "avid" supporter of Ronald Reagan\u2014 The wrestling and acting star performed at the 2000 Republican Convention, expressed admiration for President Reagan and said he has hopes for a political career when his acting days are done.\u2014 The star of the "Iron Man" and "Sherlock Holmes" movies, who spent time in prison over drug charges, is a committed conservative who once said, "You can\u2019t go from a $2,000-a-night suite at La Mirage to a penitentiary and really understand it and come out a liberal."\u2014 The star of "Sabrina The Teenage Witch" supported Mitt Romney in 2012 and is an outspoken conservative.\u2014 The one-time "Saturday Night Live" comedienne is a very active conservative who supported the presidential candidacies of Rick Santorum and Michele Bachmann.\u2014 Schneider is yet another "Saturday Night Live" alumnus who is a conservative. He has expressed admiration for former Texas Gov. Rick Perry and commented that he switched from Democrat to Republican over his concerns about Democratic influence in California.\u2014 A Christian pro-lifer, Heaton, who starred in "Everybody Loves Raymond," publicly took Rush Limbaugh's side in blasting Sandra Fluke over free birth control. She campaigned for the McCain/Palin ticket in 2008 and the Romney/Ryan ticket in 2012.\u2014 The star of "Law and Order" and "Rizzoli and Isles" considers herself a "liberal Republican." She backed Sen. John McCain and former Alaska Gov. Sarah Palin and also addressed the Republican Convention in 2004.\u2014 The star of "Wedding Crashers" and "Dodgeball" supported libertarian Ron Paul's presidential candidacies in 2008 and 2012.\u2014 The "Die Hard" star denies the label "Republican," claiming to dislike both parties, but opposes gun control and has spoken out to support the Bill of Rights.\u2014 The "Saturday Night Live" comic is a registered Republican and donated $2,100 to Rudy Giuliani's campaign for president. He also performed at the 2004 Republican Convention.\u2014 The "Nutty Professor" and longtime host of the Muscular Dystrophy Association Labor Day Telethon has blasted Obama for his failures in combating ISIS and has praised both Donald Trump and Ronald Reagan.\u2014 The tough guy star of "Walker, Texas Ranger" and martial arts movie fame is a committed Christian who supported GOP candidate Mike Huckabee in 2008 and regularly writes conservative columns for World Net Daily.\u2014 After appearing in 1979's "The Champ," Schroder went on to become a child star on TV's "Silver Spoons." A self-described "patriot to the core," Schroder spoke at the 2000 Republican National Convention in support of George W. Bush and also backed John McCain in 2008.\u2014 A registered Republican, the former "Happy Days" and "Charles in Charge" star once campaigned for Ronald Reagan and has spoken out on social media about his political beliefs. He recently endorsed Donald Trump for president.\u2014 The African-American "Clueless" star supported Mitt Romney over Obama and has been a Fox News contributor.\u2014 The rapper and actor, whose real name is James Todd Smith, is a very vocal conservative and has performed at the Republican National Convention.\u2014 The legendary country singer and "Coal Miner's Daughter" recently announced that she is supporting Donald Trump for president and has said she is willing to campaign for him.\u2014 The moniker replaces his real name of Robert James Ritchie, but nothing can replace the Republican Party in the singer/rapper's view. He has made many overseas tours to entertain American troops, and allowed the Romney campaign free use of his songs when Mitt ran for president. This campaign cycle, he endorsed Ben Carson and, later, Donald Trump.\u2014 The longtime star of the TV soap "All My Children" and Emmy winner is a well-known conservative Republican.\u2014 The one-time "teen idol" and longtime singing star is a conservative, Republican Christian who received a lifetime achievement award from the Conservative Political Action Conference.\u2014The shock rocker, whose real name is Vincent Damon Furnier, issurprisingly a hardcore born-again Christian conservative with strong Creationist beliefs.\u2014 The actor, producer, author, director, and star of "Threesome," "The Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas," and "Celebrity Apprentice" is a born-again Christian who backed Mike Huckabee for president.\u2014 The smiling host of "Wheel of Fortune" is an outspoken conservative who has challenged global warming theorists, written for the conservative magazine Human Events, and donated to Republican candidates.\u2014 The "Bat Out of Hell" rock-opera singer, "The Rocky Horror Picture Show" actor, and TV host endorsed Mitt Romney for president and has blasted the removal of prayer from public schools.\u2014 The star of "Do The Right Thing," "The Godfather Part II," and "The Last Don" is a conservative Republican who favors Ted Cruz in the current presidential race.\u2014 The actress, singer, reality television personality, and clothing designer is a registered Republican who endorsed George Bush for president in 2004 and has made numerous trips overseas to entertain American troops.
