aVDo you see Jesus in this sonogram? That's who, in addition to their daughter, a Pennsylvania couple saw in a recent image of their unborn baby.\u000a\u000aAlicia Zeek and Zac Smith both thought part of the sonogram image looks like the face of Jesus in a robe with a crown of thorns on his head, Fox43 reported.\u000a\u000a\u201cWhen they gave it to us ... umm, to me, it\u2019s Jesus. And it looks like Jesus,\u201d Zeek told the news station.\u000a\u000aSmith said he got emotional looking at the image.\u000a\u000a"It almost brought tears to my eyes," he told Fox43. "I was speechless, I just couldn\u2019t believe it, I really didn\u2019t believe what I was seeing."\u000a\u000aThe parents, who say they aren\u2019t very religious, took the sight as a comforting sign about the health of their unborn child. Their first two children were born with birth defects, Fox43 reported.\u000a\u000aThe technician and doctors confirmed baby Briella looks healthy, as well.\u000a\u000a\u201cOnce she said everything is good and we looked at the picture, I was like \u2014 look babe, we have nothing to worry about,\u201d Smith said, Fox43 reported.\u000a\u000aThe couple put the photo on Facebook to ask their friends what they saw on the sonogram. Smith called it a \u201cblessing,\u201d no matter what people saw.\u000a\u000aBriella was born on Wednesday and both mom and baby are doing well, the BBC reported.\u000a\u000aWhile many on Twitter were skeptical of seeing Jesus in a sonogram, some were more accepting of the image.\u000a\u000aI see Jesus in every sonogram.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aJeremiah 1:5 \u2014 Chris Loesch (@ChrisLoesch) August 24, 2017\u000a\u000aI was going to say something not nice, if the couple see Jesus in sonogram, then that what it is congratulations \U0001f930\U0001f3fc \u2014 toi (@toi356) August 24, 2017
